Marisa Ryan Date of birth: November 20, 1974 Place of birth: Manhattan, New York, U.S. Active: 1983-present Role: Nell Delaney Show(s): New York Undercover (regular)

Marisa Ryan (born November 20, 1974) is an American actress who portrays Nell Delaney on New York Undercover.

Biography and career[]

Marisa Ryan is best known for her role as Elizabeth Cooper-MacGillis in the CBS sitcom Major Dad (1989-1993), and as Abby Bernstein in the 2001 comedy film Wet Hot American Summer, its Netflix prequel series, Wet Hot American Summer: First Day of Camp (2015) and its Netflix sequel series Wet Hot American Summer: Ten Years Later (2017).

Ryan married actor Jeremy Sisto. They divorced in 2002, after nine years of marriage.
